    The {gt} Interactive Solution

    The linking is hard-coded into the table.

    admiraldiscovery::interactive_discovery("gt")

    The {reactable} Interactive Solution

    The linking is hard-coded into the table.

    admiraldiscovery::interactive_discovery("reactable")

    The knitr::kable() Static Solution

    Auto-linking works here.

    admiraldiscovery::discovery |> 
  head(n = 10) |> 
  dplyr::mutate(
    fn_linked = glue::glue("`{package}::{fn}()`"),
    .before = package
  ) |> 
  dplyr::select(-c("package", "fn", "fn_url")) |> 
  knitr::kable()
    dataset dataset_type variable variable_label fn_linked adam_ig_reference
    ADAE OCCDS TRTSDT Derive treatment start date admiral::derive_vars_merged() NA
    ADAE OCCDS TRTEDT Derive treatment end date admiral::derive_vars_merged() NA
    ADAE OCCDS DTHDT Derive death date admiral::derive_vars_merged() NA
    ADAE OCCDS EOSDT Derive end of study date admiral::derive_vars_merged() NA
    ADAE OCCDS ADURN Derive analysis duration admiral::derive_vars_duration() NA
    ADAE OCCDS ASTDTM Derive analysis start datetime admiral::derive_vars_dtm() NA
    ADAE OCCDS AENDTM Derive analysis end datetime admiral::derive_vars_dtm() NA
    ADAE OCCDS ASTDT Derive analysis start date variables from datetimes admiral::derive_vars_dtm_to_dt() NA
    ADAE OCCDS AENDT Derive analysis end date variables from datetimes admiral::derive_vars_dtm_to_dt() NA
    ADAE OCCDS AOCCIFL Derive occurrence flags: first occurrence of most severe adverse events admiral::restrict_derivation() NA

    The {gt} Static Solution

    Auto-linking works here.

    library(gt)

admiraldiscovery::discovery |> 
  head(n = 10) |> 
  dplyr::mutate(
    fn_linked = glue::glue("`{package}::{fn}()`"),
    .before = package
  ) |> 
  dplyr::select(-c("package", "fn", "fn_url")) |> 
  gt::gt() |> 
  fmt_markdown()
